From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kleis Auke Wolthuizen <github@kleisauke.nl>
Date: Wed, 8 Apr 2026 14:32:36 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 1/1] Reapply "globals: Don't export DllMain on Windows"

This reverts commit d87d94773e0ea963465ec0fb3b1d1b9831760d25.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [other]
This change would require downstream code to be recompiled.

diff --git a/globals.c b/globals.c
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/globals.c
+++ b/globals.c
@@ -786,11 +786,8 @@ xmlDllMain(ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED void *hinstDLL, unsigned long fdwReason,
  * Note that we do NOT want to include this function declaration in
  * a public header because it's meant to be called by Windows itself,
  * not a program that uses this library.
- *
- * It is a mistake to export this function, but changing that seems
- * to break the ABI.
  */
-XMLPUBFUN BOOL WINAPI
+BOOL WINAPI
 DllMain (HINSTANCE hinstDLL,
          DWORD     fdwReason,
          LPVOID    lpvReserved);
